article.headline: Jackson State 72, Texas Southern 54
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. (AP) -- Dakari Wallace scored 25 points to lead Jackson State to a 72-54 victory over Texas Southern Saturday night. Jackson State (10-14, 6-6 Southwestern Athletic) has won three of its last four. Wallace scored 14 points in the first half as Jackson State took a 35-32 halftime lead. He then scored the first seven points of the second half as Jackson State extended the lead to 50-36 with 13 minutes left. Sean Walker had 15 points and Mike Sneed added 14 for Texas Southern (5-14, 3-8). Catraiva Given added 12 points for Texas Southern, which has lost five straight.
